An applicant for a permit to discharge pollutants into waters of the Commonwealth shall be subject to a discharge permit fee by the cabinet upon receiving the cabinet's determination that the permit will be issued and the fee shall be equal to the cost of review but shall not exceed the following amounts:
Major industry: three thousand two hundred dollars ($3,200);
Minor industry: two thousand one hundred dollars ($2,100);
Nonprocess industry: one thousand dollars ($1,000);
Large, non-publicly-owned treatment works: one thousand seven hundred dollars ($1,700);
Intermediate, non-publicly-owned treatment works: one thousand five hundred dollars ($1,500);
Small, non-publicly-owned treatment works: one thousand dollars ($1,000);
Agriculture: one thousand two hundred dollars ($1,200); and
Surface mining operation: one thousand two hundred dollars ($1,200).
